<h1
id="build-a-simple-machine-learning-pipeline-for-predicting-house-prices">Build
a Simple Machine Learning Pipeline for Predicting House Prices</h1>
<p>Project Overview You will create a Python project that predicts house
prices using a simple linear regression model. The project will include
data preprocessing, model training, evaluation, configuration
management, logging, testing, and packaging.</p>
<h2 id="workflow">Workflow</h2>
<ul>
<li>Load and validate house price data (CSV or API).</li>
<li>Preprocess data (handle missing values, feature scaling).</li>
<li>Train a regression model (linear regression).</li>
<li>Evaluate model performance (MAE, RMSE).</li>
<li>Log results and errors.</li>
<li>Configure parameters via config files or environment variables.</li>
<li>Test each function and integration of modules.</li>
<li>Package the project for distribution.</li>
</ul>
